# SecureGate — Project Rules & Context

## What We Are Building
SecureGate is a standalone authentication app built as a Next.js 14 App Router project.
It is NOT a full product — its sole purpose is to demonstrate production-grade auth and security.
Scope is intentionally small. Do not add features beyond what is listed below.

## Tech Stack (Do Not Deviate)
- Framework: Next.js 14 with App Router and TypeScript
- Database: PostgreSQL via Prisma ORM
- Auth: NextAuth.js v5 with Credentials provider only (no social login)
- Password hashing: bcryptjs with salt rounds of 12
- Email: Resend + React Email
- Validation: Zod (server-side only)
- Rate limiting: Upstash Redis (@upstash/ratelimit + @upstash/redis)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- Deployment: Vercel

## Folder Structure
```
src/
  app/
    api/
      auth/
        [...nextauth]/route.ts
        signup/route.ts
        forgot-password/route.ts
        reset-password/route.ts
        verify-email/route.ts
    (auth)/
      login/page.tsx
      signup/page.tsx
      forgot-password/page.tsx
      reset-password/[token]/page.tsx
    verify-email/[token]/page.tsx
    dashboard/page.tsx
  lib/
    prisma.ts
    auth.ts
    email.ts
    rate-limit.ts
  components/
    PasswordStrengthIndicator.tsx
prisma/
  schema.prisma
middleware.ts
```

## Prisma Models
```prisma
model User {
  id            String    @id @default(cuid())
  name          String?
  email         String    @unique
  password      String
  emailVerified DateTime?
  createdAt     DateTime  @default(now())
}

model VerificationToken {
  identifier String
  token      String   @unique
  expires    DateTime
}

model PasswordResetToken {
  email   String
  token   String   @unique
  expires DateTime
}
```

## Security Rules (Non-Negotiable)
- NEVER store plain text passwords. Always use bcrypt.hash(password, 12)
- NEVER confirm whether an email exists. Forgot-password always returns success
- NEVER expose stack traces or internal errors in API responses
- NEVER hardcode secrets. All sensitive values go in .env.local only
- NEVER commit .env.local to GitHub
- Always validate input server-side with Zod before touching the database
- Rate limit login: max 5 attempts per IP per 10 minutes
- Rate limit forgot-password: max 3 attempts per IP per 10 minutes
- Verification tokens expire in 15 minutes
- Password reset tokens expire in 1 hour
- Use crypto.randomBytes(32).toString('hex') for all token generation

## Environment Variables Required
```
DATABASE_URL
NEXTAUTH_SECRET
NEXTAUTH_URL
RESEND_API_KEY
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN
```

## Features to Build (In Order)
1. Database schema + Prisma setup
2. NextAuth Credentials provider + signup API
3. Email verification flow (Resend)
4. Forgot password + reset password flow
5. Rate limiting middleware
6. UI polish (forms with loading states, validation messages, password strength indicator)

## UI Requirements
- Tailwind CSS only — no component libraries
- Every form: accessible labels, real error messages (not "Something went wrong"), loading state
- Password field: strength indicator showing Weak / Fair / Strong
- Login error message: "Invalid email or password" — never say which field is wrong
- Clean, dark or neutral design — minimal, functional

## What NOT to Build
- Social login (Google, GitHub, etc.)
- Multi-factor authentication
- Admin panel
- Payment integration
- Anything not listed in the Features section above

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode
- No any types
- Server components by default, use "use client" only when necessary
- API routes return proper HTTP status codes (400, 401, 429, 500)
- Prisma client is a singleton in lib/prisma.ts
